cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CE, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a novel approach for providing incentives for caching in small cell networks based on contract theory. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with designing contracts to maximize the global benefit of content providers and prevent them from manipulating the outcome of the caching process, which falls under the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Computational Economics (cs.CE) categories. Finally, the paper also considers the issue of asymmetric information, which is relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category.
